# @prisma/app-tsdown source-only policy

The package `packages/tsdown-config` (`@prisma/app-tsdown`) is the shared tsdown
base config. It is source-only and must not add emitted JavaScript artifacts to
work around runtime config loading.

## Rules

- Do not add `base.js` (or other transpiled JS siblings) in `packages/tsdown-config`.
- Do not change `packages/tsdown-config/package.json` exports to point at `.js`.
- Keep the export source-only (currently `./base.ts`), and keep the package
  `private: true` — it is never published.

## Rationale

- It is an internal config helper and should remain canonical TypeScript source
  imported by each package's `tsdown.config.ts`.
- Workarounds for runtime loading must be solved in consumers/tooling, not by
  emitting parallel JS files here.
